QUERY:  does marijuana cause heart attack
DATE: 01-29-2025
Yes, marijuana use can increase the risk of heart attack and stroke. The risk increases with more frequent use. [1, 2, 3, 4]
Daily use
Daily cannabis use is associated with a 25% increased risk of heart attack and a 42% increased risk of stroke. [1, 2]
Weekly use
Weekly cannabis use is associated with a 3% increased risk of heart attack and a 5% increased risk of stroke. [1]
More than once a month
Smoking marijuana more than once a month is associated with an increased risk of heart attack and heart disease. [3]

Why does marijuana increase the risk of heart attack? [3]
The psychoactive component of marijuana, THC, causes inflammation in the endothelial cells that line blood vessels. [3]
The risk of heart attack and stroke increases with more frequent use, similar to the risk of using tobacco or alcohol. [1, 5]
Who should avoid marijuana? [5]
People with pre-existing heart disease should avoid marijuana smoking. [5]
People should avoid driving or operating machinery within 6 hours of consuming cannabis. [6]
Other effects of marijuana [6]
Marijuana can cause dry mouth and throat, heart palpitations, dizziness, and drowsiness.

